data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider has been removed entirely**. The provider is now async-only — no configuration flag can re-enable synchronous execution.

Every call to `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` will throw an **`InvalidOperationException`** at runtime.

### The fix — convert to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return types become `Task<T>` / `Task`
- Methods gain `async` modifier and `Async` suffix
- All LINQ terminal operators use their `Async` counterparts
- Callers up the chain must also be updated to `await`

You can also remove any `EnableSyncOverAsync()` / `AllowSynchronousIO` configuration from your `DbContext` setup — it's no longer recognized.
